newmac                                macro                               newmac

NAME
     nneewwmmaacc - re-read the standard macro definitions

SYNOPSIS

     nneewwmmaacc

DESCRIPTION

     This macro is used to re-read the standard macro definitions without
     starting fresh and thus losing one's current state.  It can be used after
     installing a new version of the macros, or if you want to recover the
     original definitions of any standard macros you may have redefined.

GLOBALS

     SSPPEECCDD - the name of ssppeecc's auxiliary file directory.

     SSPPEECC - the name of the current geometry, as in ffoouurrcc, zzaaxxiiss, etc.

SEE ALSO

     _d_o _q_d_o

